ABSTRACT = {The smart energy system, viewed as an &ldquo;Energy Internet&rdquo;, consists of the intelligent integration of decentralized sustainable energy sources, efficient distribution, and optimized power consumption. That implies the fault diagnosis for a smart energy system should be of low complexity. In this paper, we propose a Strong Tracking Unscented Kalman Filter (    S T U K F    ) and modified Bayes&rsquo; classification-based Modified Three Sigma test (    M T S    ), abbreviated as     S F B T    , for smart energy networks. The theoretical analysis and simulations indicate that     S F B T     detects faults with a high accuracy and a low complexity of     O ( n )    .},
